{{see|Tor}}
==English==
===Etymology===
{{AS.}} ''torr''; cf. Gaelic ''torr''. Cf. [[tower]].

===Pronunciation===
IPA: [[WEAE]] /tɛɹ/

===Noun===
# A tower; a turret.
# (Prov. Eng.) High-pointed hill; a rocky pinnacle. 

====Quotations====
<BLOCKQUOTE>
The moon was low upon the right, and the jagged pinnacle of a granite tor
stood up against the lower curve of its silver disc.<BR>
&mdash;A. Conan Doyle in ''The Hound of the Baskervilles''
</blockquote>

